CWE: CWE-119 Improper Restriction of Operations within the Bounds of a Memory Buffer
Vulnerability: Multiple stack-based buffer overflows in Aurigma Image Uploader ActiveX control (ImageUploader4.ocx) 4.6.17.0, 4.5.70.0, and 4.5.126.0, and ImageUploader5 5.0.10.0, as used by Facebook PhotoUploader 4.5.57.0, allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via long (1) ExtractExif and (2) ExtractIptc properties.
Improper handling of close_notify alerts can result in an out-of-bounds read in AsyncSSLSocket. This issue affects folly prior to v2019.11.04.00.
